==Korean==

===Verb===
'''가다''' (ga-da)
# To [[go]], cf. Dutch [[gaan]], German [[gehen]] 

====Antonyms====
* [[오다]] (o-da) To [[come]]

====See also====
* [[걷다]] (geod-da, geot-) To [walk]] 
* [[거닐다]] (geonil-da) To [[go]] while walking  
* [[노닐다]] (nonil-da) To [[go]] while playing
* [[니다]] (ni-da) (obsolete) To [[go]] 
* [[닐다]] (nil-da) (obsolete) To [[go]], cf. Latin [[ire]] 
* [[다니다]] (dani-da) To [[attend]]
* [[바닥]] (badag, badak) [[bottom]], [[bed]], [[base]], cf. [[buttock]]s, [[fathom]] 
* [[받다]] (bad-da, bat-) To [[receive]], [[support]], [[bear]], [[butt]] 
* [[발]] (bal) [[foot]] 
* [[밟다]] (balb-da, balp-) To [[step]], [[tread]], [[walk]], [[wade]] through water, cf. Latin [[vadere]] "to step, go"
*[[밭]] (bat) (farming) [[bed]], [[field]], [[garden]], [[pad]], [[patch]] 
* [[이르다]] (ireu-da) To [[arrive]], cf. Latin [[ire]]  

